{"input": "What is 2 + 2?", "expected_output": "4"}
{"input": "Write a Python function to reverse a string.", "expected_output": "def reverse_string(s): return s[::-1]"}
{"input": "What are SOLID principles in software engineering?", "expected_output": "SOLID stands for Single Responsibility, Open/Closed, Liskov Substitution, Interface Segregation, and Dependency Inversion."}
{"input": "Explain asyncio in Python.", "expected_output": "asyncio is Python's standard library for writing concurrent code using async/await syntax and an event loop."}
{"input": "What is the difference between authentication and authorization?", "expected_output": "Authentication verifies who you are; authorization determines what you are allowed to do."}
